<p>
    Bootstrap uses <code>@media</code> queries to create a <strong>mobile first</strong> responsive design. The available sizes are: <code>xs</code>, <code>sm</code>, <code>md</code>, and <code>lg</code>.
    <br />
    Mobile first means that larger sizes inherit smaller sizes, and smaller sizes default to 12.
    <br />
    Therefore at size <code>md</code> a <code>.col-sm-4</code> is the same size as a <code>.col-md-4</code>, but a <code>.col-lg-4</code> will be the same size as a <code>.col-md-12</code>.
</p>

